ing What God Loves: 4th Sunday of Advent</span></div> <div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(128, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Whenever I asked people to describe God I will usually do it in this way, finish the sentence, God is ... (blank). Invariably people will respond God is love.</span></div> <div><br></div> <div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(128, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Do we believe God is love?</span></div> <div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(128, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Do we believe in a God of love?</span></div> <div><br></div> <div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(128, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Love is a special and complicated emotion which is quite difficult to understand. I think we would all agree with that. As Christian people we are called to love and to love some more ... and after that love some more. What does that look like?</span></div> <div><br></div> <div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(128, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Join us on Sunday and we will dig a little deeper into what it means to love what God loves.</span></div> <div><br></div> <div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(128, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Blessings,</span></div> <div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: rgb(128, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Jim</span></div> </div></div> </td> </tr> </tbody> </table> </div> </td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" class=\"galileo-ap-layout-editor\" style=\"min-width: 100%;\"> <tbody> <tr> <td class=\" editor-col OneColumnMobile\" width=\"100%\" align=\"\" valign=\"top\"> <div class=\"gl-contains-divider\"> <table class=\"editor-divider\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"